<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=999&amp;p=8657#p8657"><![CDATA[
NESASM banks are always 8 KB no matter the capabilities of the mapper you're targeting. What you're seeing with an NROM that takes 3 NESASM banks is one bank loaded into CPU $8000 and $C000, one bank loaded into CPU $A000 and $E000, and one bank loaded into PPU$0000.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jan 26, 2006 10:12 pm</p><hr />
