<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=999&amp;p=8571#p8571"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />On PPU cycle 257 (if the background or sprites are enabled) or the second write to $2006, the VRAM register equals the temporary VRAM register.<br /></div><br /><br />Note that on cycle 257 only the X-scroll related bits are copied to the real VRAM register (bits 0-4, 10).  Other bits are unaffected.<br /><br />The only time the address is copied in full (aside from the second $2006 write) is on the pre-render scanline on cycle 304.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Wed Jan 25, 2006 11:14 am</p><hr />
